  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'cdc-natural-disasters-power-outage-chunk-0002',
      title: 'What to Do to Protect Yourself During a Power Outage | Natural Disasters | CDC #2 CO is found in combustion fumes, such as those p',
      summary: 'CO is found in combustion fumes, such as those produced by small gasoline engines, stoves, generators, lanterns, and gas ranges, or by burning charcoal and wood.',
      steps: [
        'CO from these sources can build up in enclosed or partially enclosed spaces.',
        'People and animals in these spaces can be poisoned and can die from breathing CO.',
        'Never use a generator, pressure washer, or any gasoline-powered engine inside your home, basement, or garage or less than 20 feet from any window, door, or vent.',
        'Use an extension cord that is more than 20 feet long to keep the generator at a safe distance.',
      ],
