  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'nps-campfires-chunk-0003',
      title: 'Campfires (U.S. National Park Service) #3 Don’t assume a bonfire is going to be ok in a bu',
      summary: 'Don’t assume a bonfire is going to be ok in a busy campground full of kids, RVs and trees.',
      steps: [
        'Ask at the visitor center or find the campground host to see if specific areas are set aside for fires, and if there are rules on the size of your blaze.',
        'Making a Fire Before starting your campfire, take a look around your campsite to make sure your tent, gear, and any other flammable objects are at least 15 feet away and upwind of the firepit.',
        'Buying or using local kindling/wood Kindling and wood should be bought near the campground (or collected from the area, if the rules permit doing that - keep in mind, this is not allowed in many national parks).',
        'Bringing wood from far away might also bring along pests that will flee your burning wood and potentially invade and cause problems in their new environment.',
      ],
