      title: 'Wilderness Travel Basics - Olympic National Park (U.S. National Park Service) #9 Travel in small parties and spread out to preven',
      summary: 'Travel in small parties and spread out to prevent damage to fragile plants.',
      steps: [
        'When traveling cross-country, follow good Leave No Trace practices.',
        'Off-trail hiking is permitted throughout the Olympic Wilderness.',
        'Before You Go: Let a friend or family member know your route and plans.',
