      title: 'FM 21-76 Survival Manual #181 Page 116.',
      summary: 'Page 116.',
      steps: [
        '8-1 Chapter 8 Food Procurement One of man’s most urgent requirements is food.',
        'In contemplating virtually any hypothetical survival situation, the mind immediately turns to thoughts of food.',
        'Unless the situation occurs in an arid environment, even water, which is more important to maintaining body functions, will usually follow food in our initial thoughts.',
