      title: 'FM 21-76 Survival Manual #497 Page 312.',
      summary: 'Page 312.',
      steps: [
        'FM 3-05.70 18-5 USING THE MOON 18-8.',
        'Because the moon has no light of its own, we can only see it when it reflects the sun’s light.',
        'As it orbits the earth on its 28-day circuit, the shape of the reflected light varies according to its position.',
        'We say there is a new moon or no moon when it is on the opposite side of the earth from the sun.',
