      title: 'FM 21-76 Survival Manual #498 Page 312.',
      summary: 'Page 312.',
      steps: [
        'The main constellations to learn are the Ursa Major, also known as the Big Dipper or the Plow, and Cassiopeia, also known as the Lazy W (Figure 18-3, page 18-6).',
        'Use them to locate Polaris, also known as the polestar or the North Star.',
        'Polaris is considered to remain stationary, as it rotates only 1.08 degrees around the northern celestial pole.',
        'The North Star is the last star of the Little Dipper’s handle and can be confused with the Big Dipper.',
      ],
