      title: 'FM 21-76 Survival Manual #742 Page 487.',
      summary: 'Page 487.',
      steps: [
        'FM 3-05.70 B-97 Water lily Nymphaea odorata Description: These plants have large, triangular leaves that float on the water’s surface, large, fragrant flow ers that are usually white, or red, and thick, fleshy rhizomes that grow in the mud.',
        'Habitat and Distribution: Water lilies are found throughout much of the temperate and subtropical regions.',
        'Edible Parts: The flowers, seeds, and rhizomes are edible raw or cooked.',
        'To prepare rhizomes for eating, peel off the corky rind.',
      ],
