      steps: [
        'FM 3-05.70 B-102 Wild dock and wild sorrel Rumex crispus and Rumex acetosella Description: Wild dock is a stout plant with most of its leaves at the base of its stem that is commonly 15 to 30 centimeters (6 to 12 inches) long.',
        'The plants usually develop from a strong, fleshy, ca rrotlike taproot.',
