      title: 'FM 21-76 Survival Manual #795 Page 535.',
      summary: 'Page 535.',
      steps: [
        'Rattlesnakes, copperheads, cottonmouths, and several species of dangerous snakes from Central and South America, Asia, China, and India fall into the pit viper group.',
        'The pit is a highly sensitive organ capable of picking up the slightest temperature variance.',
        'Most pit vipers are nocturnal.',
        'They hunt for food at night with the aid of these specialized pits that let them locate prey in total darkness.',
