  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-burns-chunk-0003',
      title: 'Burns - Injuries and Poisoning - MSD Manual Consumer Version #3 When children and older adults are burned, docto',
      summary: 'When children and older adults are burned, doctors also consider the possibility that the person was abused (see Child Neglect and Abuse and Elder Abuse ).',
      steps: [
        'Classification of Burns Doctors classify burns according to strict, widely accepted definitions.',
        'The definitions classify the burn’s depth and the extent of tissue damage.',
        'Burn depth The depth of injury from a burn is described as superficial, partial thickness, or full thickness: Superficial burns are the most shallow (also called first-degree burns).',
        'They affect only the top layer of skin (epidermis).',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
