  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-burns-chunk-0004',
      title: 'Burns - Injuries and Poisoning - MSD Manual Consumer Version #4 Estimating the Extent of a Burn To determine the',
      summary: 'Estimating the Extent of a Burn To determine the severity of a burn, doctors estimate what percentage of the body’s surface has partial-thickness or full-thickness burns.',
      steps: [
        'For adults, doctors use the rule of nines.',
        'This method divides almost all of the body into sections of 9% or of 2 times 9% (18%).',
        'For children, doctors use charts that adjust these percentages according to the child’s age (Lund-Browder charts).',
        'Adjustment is needed because different areas of the body grow at different rates.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
