  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-burns-chunk-0006',
      title: 'Burns - Injuries and Poisoning - MSD Manual Consumer Version #6 Moderate and severe burns : Burns involving the',
      summary: 'Moderate and severe burns : Burns involving the hands, feet, face, or genitals, partial-thickness burns involving more than 10% of the body surface area, and all full-thickness bur',
      steps: [
        'Symptoms of Burns Symptoms of a burn wound vary with the burn’s depth: Superficial burns are red, swollen, and painful.',
        'The burned area whitens (blanches) when lightly touched but does not develop blisters.',
        'Partial-thickness burns are pink or red, swollen, and extremely painful.',
        'Within 24 hours (often shortly after the burn), blisters usually develop that may ooze a clear fluid.',
      ],
