  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-burns-chunk-0007',
      title: 'Burns - Injuries and Poisoning - MSD Manual Consumer Version #7 The deepest burns may cause the least pain, beca',
      summary: 'The deepest burns may cause the least pain, because the nerves that sense pain are destroyed.',
      steps: [
        'Complications of Burns Minor burns are usually superficial and do not cause complications.',
        'However, deep partial-thickness and full-thickness burns swell and take more time to heal.',
        'In addition, deeper burns can cause scar tissue to form.',
        'This scar tissue shrinks (contracts) as it heals.',
      ],
