  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-burns-chunk-0010',
      title: 'Burns - Injuries and Poisoning - MSD Manual Consumer Version #10 Treatment of Burns For minor burns, cooling the',
      summary: 'Treatment of Burns For minor burns, cooling the wound with room temperature water for several minutes, followed by wound care and dressing For severe burns, hospitalization and tre',
      steps: [
        'For example, fires are extinguished.',
        'Clothing—especially any that is smoldering (such as melted synthetic shirts), covered with a hot substance (for example, tar), or soaked with chemicals—is immediately removed.',
        'Hospitalization is sometimes necessary for optimal care of burns.',
        'For example, extensive partial-thickness or full-thickness burns require treatment with intravenous fluids; elevating a severely burned arm or leg above the level of the heart to prevent swelling is more easily accommodated in a hospital.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
