  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-burns-chunk-0012',
      title: 'Burns - Injuries and Poisoning - MSD Manual Consumer Version #12 The salves prevent infection and form a seal to',
      summary: 'The salves prevent infection and form a seal to prevent further bacteria from entering the wound.',
      steps: [
        'A sterile bandage is then applied to protect the burned area from dirt and further injury.',
        'A tetanus vaccination is given if needed.',
        'Care at home includes keeping the burn clean to prevent infection.',
        'In addition, many people are given analgesics (pain relievers), sometimes opioids , for at least a few days.',
