  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-emergency-priorities-chunk-0001',
      title: 'Emergency First Aid Priorities - Injuries and Poisoning - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Emergency First Aid Priorities By Jaime Jordan ,',
      summary: 'Emergency First Aid Priorities By Jaime Jordan , MD , UCLA School of Medicine Reviewed/Revised Modified Jul 2024 v829360 The first priority during a medical emergency is to save li',
      steps: [
        'A person who is unconscious and unresponsive may be close to death, and rescuers must assess the situation and begin treatment as needed to restore and maintain the person\'s a irway , b reathing , and c irculation (the ABCs).',
        'A problem in any of these areas may be fatal if not corrected quickly.',
        'The airway, which is the passage through which air travels to the lungs, can become blocked (for example, by choking on or inhaling a piece of food).',
        'Many disorders, such as emphysema and asthma , can make breathing difficult.',
      ],
