      title: 'Emergency First Aid Priorities - Injuries and Poisoning - MSD Manual Consumer Version #5 A description of how a person became injured and',
      summary: 'A description of how a person became injured and other information from bystanders, family members, or rescuers can be essential to the person\'s treatment.',
      steps: [
        'People who do not need urgent treatment are provided reassurance and simple measures, such as having a blanket supplied and being kept calm and warm, while they wait to be treated.',
        'To prevent the spread of blood-borne infections, rescuers should protect themselves by following universal precautions, which is an approach to preventing transmission of infection by considering all human blood and body fluids to be potentially infectious.',
