  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0002-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Anemia Due to Excessive Bleeding - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 However, over time, bleeding reduces the amount',
      summary: 'However, over time, bleeding reduces the amount of iron in the body, so that the bone marrow is not able to increase production of new red blood cells to replace those lost.',
      steps: [
        'Rapid blood loss The symptoms may be severe initially, especially if anemia develops rapidly as a result of the sudden loss of blood due to an injury, surgery, childbirth, or a ruptured blood vessel.',
        'Losing large amounts of blood suddenly can create 2 problems: Blood pressure falls because the amount of fluid left in the blood vessels is insufficient.',
        'The body’s oxygen supply is drastically reduced because the number of oxygen-carrying red blood cells has decreased so quickly.',
        'Either problem may lead to a heart attack , stroke , or death.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
      escalation: '原始来源：MSD Manual / Anemia Due to Excessive Bleeding - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version',
