      title: 'Sickle Cell Disease - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 (See also Overview of Anemia .) Sickle cell dise',
      summary: '(See also Overview of Anemia .) Sickle cell disease most frequently affects people with African or Black American ancestry.',
      steps: [
        'About 8% of people with such ancestry in the United States have 1 copy of the gene for sickle cell disease (that is, they have sickle cell trait).',
