      title: 'Formation of Blood Cells - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 Certain conditions may trigger additional produc',
      summary: 'Certain conditions may trigger additional production of blood cells.',
      steps: [
        'When the oxygen content of body tissues is low or the number of red blood cells decreases, the kidneys produce and release erythropoietin , a hormone that stimulates the bone marrow to produce more red blood cells.',
        'The bone marrow produces and releases more white blood cells in response to infections.',
        'To respond to bleeding, the bone marrow produces and releases more platelets.',
        'Effects of aging on the blood Aging has some effect on bone marrow and blood cells, resulting in less cell-producing bone marrow.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
