  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0018-chunk-0001',
      title: 'Protein Disorders Causing Bruising or Bleeding - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Protein Disorders Causing Bruising or Bleeding B',
      summary: 'Protein Disorders Causing Bruising or Bleeding By David J.',
      steps: [
        'Kuter , MD, DPhil , Harvard Medical School Reviewed/Revised Modified Feb 2025 v8302927 Multimedia | Conditions that cause an abnormal protein or an abnormal amount of certain normal proteins in the blood can cause blood vessels to become fragile.',
        'When these fragile blood vessels break, people develop red or purple bruises (purpura) on the skin.',
        'Conditions that may cause purpura include Amyloidosis Cryoglobulinemia Hypergammaglobulinemic purpura Hyperviscosity syndrome Amyloidosis Amyloidosis causes the protein amyloid to be deposited within blood vessels in the skin and subcutaneous tissues, which may increase the fragility of the blood vessels, causing red or purple bruises, usually on the arms.',
        'When a person develops bruising around the eyes or bruising after only light stroking, doctors may suspect amyloidosis.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
      escalation: '原始来源：MSD Manual / Protein Disorders Causing Bruising or Bleeding - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version',
