  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0021-chunk-0001',
      title: 'Disseminated Intravascular Coagulation (DIC) - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Disseminated Intravascular Coagulation (DIC) By',
      summary: 'Disseminated Intravascular Coagulation (DIC) By Michael B.',
      steps: [
        'Streiff , MD , Johns Hopkins University School of Medicine Reviewed/Revised Modified Jul 2025 v775296 Disseminated intravascular coagulation is a condition in which small blood clots develop throughout the bloodstream, blocking small blood vessels.',
        'The increased clotting depletes the platelets and clotting factors needed to control bleeding, causing excessive bleeding.',
        'Symptoms | Diagnosis | Treatment | Multimedia | There are a number of possible causes, including infection, surgery, and complications of childbirth.',
        'Excessive clotting is followed by excessive bleeding.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
