  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0024-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Uncommon Inherited Clotting Disorders - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 Bleeding that is difficult to control after inju',
      summary: 'Bleeding that is difficult to control after injury or surgery in a person who does not have hemophilia may indicate that a person has an uncommon clotting disorder.',
      steps: [
        'Doctors measure the levels of clotting factors in a blood sample in people who experience bruising or bleeding that is difficult to control.',
        'Lab Test Coagulation Factor Tests Treatment depends on the specific factor that is deficient but usually includes replacing the deficient clotting factor.',
        'Some other clotting disorders include: Factor XI deficiency Deficiency of factor XI is the most common of the rare inherited clotting disorders.',
        'About half of cases of factor XI deficiency occur among people of Eastern European Jewish ancestry.',
      ],
