  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0027-chunk-0001',
      title: 'Apheresis - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Apheresis By Ravindra Sarode , MD , The Universi',
      summary: 'Apheresis By Ravindra Sarode , MD , The University of Texas Southwestern Medical Center Reviewed/Revised Modified Mar 2026 v42282802 In apheresis, blood is removed from a person an',
      steps: [
        'Apheresis can be used to: Obtain healthy blood components from a donor to transfuse to a person with a disorder Remove harmful substances or excessive numbers of blood cells from the blood of a person with a disorder (termed therapeutic apheresis) The different components of blood that can be separated include: Red blood cells Platelets Plasma White blood cells Plasma contains antibodies (immunoglobulins) and clotting factors , which are sometimes separated from plasma.',
        'The 2 most common types of apheresis that are used to remove harmful substances from blood are: Plasma exchange Cytapheresis Cytapheresis may have different names, depending on the type of cell that is removed from the blood.',
        'Plateletpheresis: Platelet removal Leukapheresis: White blood cell removal When plasma is separated from the blood, the procedure is called plasmapheresis .',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
      escalation: '原始来源：MSD Manual / Apheresis - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version',
