  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0032-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Special Blood Donation and Transfusion Procedures - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 Double red blood cell donation (apheresis red bl',
      summary: 'Double red blood cell donation (apheresis red blood cell donation) In the so-called double red blood cell donation (apheresis red blood cell donations), a person donates twice as m',
      steps: [
        'This double donation is possible because the person gives only red blood cells rather than whole blood.',
        'Whole blood is drawn from the donor, and a machine that separates the blood into its components selectively removes the red blood cells and returns the rest of the blood components (platelets and plasma ) to the donor.',
        'Some fluid is also given to the donor intravenously because otherwise, the donor\'s blood pressure could become low enough to cause symptoms, such as light-headedness or loss of consciousness.',
        'After double red blood cell donation, people may be less able to exercise vigorously for a few days.',
      ],
