  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0036-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Overview of Iron Overload - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 Symptoms and complications can occur if iron acc',
      summary: 'Symptoms and complications can occur if iron accumulates in the endocrine organs (especially the pancreas, gonads, and pituitary gland), liver, or heart.',
      steps: [
        'Taking in a large amount of iron all at once, such as in an overdose of iron pills, can be very dangerous.',
        'Iron poisoning damages the digestive tract, liver, heart, and brain, and it can be fatal.',
        'African iron overload occurs most often in sub-Saharan Africa among people who consume an iron-rich fermented drink.',
        'A genetic component is thought to contribute to the development of African iron overload, but no gene has yet been identified.',
      ],
