  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0039-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Myelofibrosis - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 In myelofibrosis, the fibroblasts make too much',
      summary: 'In myelofibrosis, the fibroblasts make too much fibrous tissue, which crowds out the blood-producing cells.',
      steps: [
        'When this occurs, some blood-producing cells migrate from the bone marrow to the spleen and liver.',
        'Overall, red blood cell production decreases, and anemia develops, becoming progressively more severe.',
        'In addition, many of the red blood cells that are produced are immature or misshapen.',
        'Some immature white blood cells and platelets also may be present in the blood.',
      ],
