  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0041-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Polycythemia Vera - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 Increased production of red blood cells is calle',
      summary: 'Increased production of red blood cells is called erythrocytosis .',
      steps: [
        'Sometimes people with polycythemia vera have only increased red blood cell production, but usually increased red blood cell production by itself is due to another cause.',
        'In polycythemia vera, the excess of red blood cells increases the volume of blood and makes it thicker, so that it flows less easily through small blood vessels.',
        'Polycythemia vera occurs in about 2 in every 100,000 people.',
        'The average age at which the disorder is diagnosed is 60 years, but it also occurs in younger people, of whom more women than men develop the disease.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
      escalation: '原始来源：MSD Manual / Polycythemia Vera - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version',
