  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0042-chunk-0001',
      title: 'Secondary Erythrocytosis - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Secondary Erythrocytosis (Secondary Polycythemia',
      summary: 'Secondary Erythrocytosis (Secondary Polycythemia) By Jane Liesveld , MD , James P.',
      steps: [
        'Wilmot Cancer Institute, University of Rochester Medical Center Reviewed/Revised Modified Sept 2025 v38394071 Erythrocytosis is increased production of red blood cells (erythrocytes).',
        'Symptoms | Diagnosis | Treatment | (See also Overview of Myeloproliferative Neoplasms .) Erythrocytosis may be: Primary: Caused by a disorder of the blood-forming cells Secondary: Caused by a disorder that triggers increased production by normal blood-forming cells Primary erythrocytosis occurs as a result of polycythemia vera , a myeloproliferative neoplasm in which abnormal cells in the bone marrow produce too many red blood cells along with excessive numbers of white blood cells and platelets.',
        'Occasionally, only red blood cell production is increased.',
        'Secondary erythrocytosis develops generally as a result of a disorder that increases erythropoietin secretion.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
      escalation: '原始来源：MSD Manual / Secondary Erythrocytosis - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version',
