  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0048-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Overview of Plasma Cell Disorders - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 As a result, this clone produces vast amounts of',
      summary: 'As a result, this clone produces vast amounts of a single antibody (monoclonal antibody) known as the M-protein.',
      steps: [
        'In some cases (such as with monoclonal gammopathies), the antibody produced is incomplete, consisting of only light chains or heavy chains (functional antibodies normally consist of 2 pairs of 2 different chains called a light chain and heavy chain).',
        'The abnormal plasma cells and the antibodies they produce are limited to 1 type, and levels of other types of antibodies that help fight infections fall.',
        'Thus, people with plasma cell disorders are often at higher risk of infections.',
        'The ever-increasing number of abnormal plasma cells also invades and damages various tissues and organs, and the antibody produced by the clone of plasma cells can sometimes damage vital organs, especially the kidneys and bones.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
      escalation: '原始来源：MSD Manual / Overview of Plasma Cell Disorders - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version',
