  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0050-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Immune Thrombocytopenia (ITP) - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 The blood usually contains about 140,000 to 440,',
      summary: 'The blood usually contains about 140,000 to 440,000 platelets per microliter (140 to 440 &#215; 10 9 per liter ).',
      steps: [
        'When the platelet count falls below about 50,000 platelets per microliter of blood (less than 50 &#215; 10 9 per liter), bleeding can occur even after relatively minor injury.',
        'The most serious risk of bleeding, however, generally does not occur until the platelet count falls below 10,000 to 20,000 platelets per microliter (10 to 20 &#215; 10 9 per liter) of blood.',
        'At these very low levels, bleeding may occur without any recognized injury.',
        'Immune thrombocytopenia is a disorder in which antibodies form and destroy the body\'s platelets.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
      escalation: '原始来源：MSD Manual / Immune Thrombocytopenia (ITP) - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version',
