  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0051-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Overview of Platelet Disorders - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 Neither of these conditions is serious, and most',
      summary: 'Neither of these conditions is serious, and most affected people have no problems resulting from either one.',
      steps: [
        'Platelet disorders include An abnormal increase in platelets ( essential thrombocythemia and reactive thrombocytosis ) A decrease in platelets ( thrombocytopenia ) Platelet dysfunction Any of these disorders can cause problems with blood clotting.',
        'In essential thrombocythemia , the bone marrow cells that make platelets grow excessively and make too many platelets despite no other disorder being identified.',
        'Surprisingly, the increased number of platelets may cause excessive bleeding rather than clotting.',
        'Doctors sometimes give people aspirin to lower the risk of abnormal clotting if they have certain disorders that affect blood vessels (vascular diseases) or are at increased risk of a heart attack.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
      escalation: '原始来源：MSD Manual / Overview of Platelet Disorders - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version',
