  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0052-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Overview of Thrombocytopenia - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 The blood usually contains about 140,000 to 440,',
      summary: 'The blood usually contains about 140,000 to 440,000 platelets per microliter (140 to 440 &#215; 10 9 per liter).',
      steps: [
        'When the platelet count falls below about 50,000 platelets per microliter of blood (50 &#215; 10 9 per liter), bleeding can occur even after relatively minor injury.',
        'The most serious risk of bleeding, however, generally does not occur until the platelet count falls below 10,000 to 20,000 platelets per microliter of blood (10 to 20 &#215; 10 9 per liter).',
        'At these very low levels, bleeding may occur without any recognized injury.',
        'Causes of Thrombocytopenia Many disorders can cause thrombocytopenia, but these disorders fall into 3 main categories: Too few platelets are produced Too many platelets are destroyed Too many platelets are trapped in the spleen Thrombocytopenia can occur when the bone marrow does not produce enough platelets, as happens in leukemia or other bone marrow disorders.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
      escalation: '原始来源：MSD Manual / Overview of Thrombocytopenia - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version',
