      id: 'merck-home-topic-0054-chunk-0001',
      title: 'Thrombotic Thrombocytopenic Purpura (TTP) - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Thrombotic Thrombocytopenic Purpura (TTP) By Dav',
      summary: 'Thrombotic Thrombocytopenic Purpura (TTP) By David J.',
      steps: [
        'Kuter , MD, DPhil , Harvard Medical School Reviewed/Revised Modified May 2024 v44196864 Thrombotic thrombocytopenic purpura (TTP) is a serious disorder that involves the formation of small blood clots throughout the body that block the flow of blood to vital organs such as the brain, heart, and kidneys.',
        'Symptoms | Diagnosis | Treatment | Symptoms are related to where in the body blood clots form.',
        'Diagnosis is based on the person\'s symptoms and blood test results.',
        'Treatment of TTP is with plasma exchange, corticosteroids, rituximab , and rarely caplacizumab .',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
