  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0057-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Overview of the Spleen - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 The red pulp contains other white blood cells ca',
      summary: 'The red pulp contains other white blood cells called phagocytes that ingest microorganisms, such as bacteria, fungi, and viruses.',
      steps: [
        'It also monitors red blood cells, destroying those that are abnormal or too old or damaged to function properly.',
        'In addition, the red pulp serves as a reservoir for different elements of the blood, especially white blood cells and platelets (cell-like particles involved in clotting).',
        'However, releasing these elements is a minor function of the red pulp.',
        'Viewing the Spleen Asplenia People can live without a spleen (a condition called asplenia).',
      ],
