      title: 'Bone Marrow Examination - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Bone Marrow Examination By David J.',
      summary: 'Bone Marrow Examination By David J.',
      steps: [
        'Kuter , MD, DPhil , Harvard Medical School Reviewed/Revised Jun 2025 | Modified Jul 2025 v12857211 Multimedia | Red blood cells , most white blood cells , and platelets are produced in the bone marrow, the soft fatty tissue inside bone cavities.',
        'Sometimes a sample of bone marrow must be examined to determine why blood cells are abnormal or why there are too few or too many of a specific kind of blood cell.',
        'A doctor can take two different types of bone marrow samples: Bone marrow aspirate: Removes fluid and cells by inserting a needle into the bone marrow and sucking out (aspirating) fluid and cells Bone marrow core biopsy: Removes an intact piece of bone marrow using a coring device (similar to a large diameter needle) The bone marrow aspirate shows what cells, normal and abnormal, are present in the bone marrow and provides information about their size, volume, and other characteristics.',
        'Special tests, such as cultures for bacteria, fungi, or viruses, chromosomal analysis , and analysis of cell surface proteins can be done on the sample.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
      escalation: '原始来源：MSD Manual / Bone Marrow Examination - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version',
