  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0062-chunk-0001',
      title: 'Symptoms of Blood Disorders - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Symptoms of Blood Disorders By David J.',
      summary: 'Symptoms of Blood Disorders By David J.',
      steps: [
        'Kuter , MD, DPhil , Harvard Medical School Reviewed/Revised Jun 2025 | Modified Jul 2025 v773991 Multimedia | Blood disorders can cause various symptoms in almost any area of the body.',
        'Most commonly, symptoms are caused by decreases in the blood components.',
        'Decreased red blood cells and hemoglobin can cause symptoms of anemia , such as fatigue, weakness, and shortness of breath.',
        'Decreased white blood cells or immune system proteins can cause recurrent fever and infections .',
      ],
