  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0066-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Porphyria Cutanea Tarda - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 (See also Overview of Porphyrias .) Porphyria cu',
      summary: '(See also Overview of Porphyrias .) Porphyria cutanea tarda occurs throughout the world.',
      steps: [
        'There are 2 main types: Type 1: Acquired or sporadic (in about 75 to 80% of people) Type 2: Hereditary or familial (in about 20 to 25% of people) There is a very rare type 3 that occurs in less than 1% of people.',
        'As far as is known, the sporadic form of this porphyria is the only porphyria that can occur in people who do not have an inherited deficiency of an enzyme involved in heme production.',
        'Porphyria cutanea tarda results from underactivity of the enzyme uroporphyrinogen decarboxylase, which leads to accumulation of porphyrins in the liver.',
        'Liver disease is common.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
