  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0069-chunk-0001',
      title: 'High White Blood Cell Count - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 High White Blood Cell Count (Leukocytosis) By Da',
      summary: 'High White Blood Cell Count (Leukocytosis) By David C.',
      steps: [
        'Dale , MD , University of Washington Reviewed/Revised Modified Feb 2025 v38394551 White blood cells (leukocytes) are an important part of the body’s defense against infectious organisms and foreign substances ( the immune system ).',
        'The number of white blood cells (white cell count) is normally less than 11,000 cells per microliter of blood (11 × 10 9 per liter).',
        'The most common cause of an increase in the white blood cell count is The normal response of the body to an infection Other causes include Certain medications, such as corticosteroids Cancers of the bone marrow (such as leukemia ) Release of immature or abnormal white blood cells from the bone marrow into the blood There are many types of white blood cell (see Overview of White Blood Cell Disorders ), and each type may be increased.',
        'However, most commonly, people have an Increase in neutrophils Increase in lymphocytes Test your Knowledge Take a Quiz!',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
      escalation: '原始来源：MSD Manual / High White Blood Cell Count - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version',
