      title: 'Monocyte Disorders - Blood Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 However, people may have symptoms of the disorde',
      summary: 'However, people may have symptoms of the disorder that caused the change in monocyte number.',
      steps: [
        'Diagnosis is by blood testing (complete blood count) done when a person has signs or symptoms of an infection or autoimmune disorder.',
        'Sometimes the condition is discovered by chance when a complete blood count is done during a routine physical or for the evaluation of another condition.',
