      title: 'Joints - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 (Collagen is a tough fibrous tissue, and proteog',
      summary: '(Collagen is a tough fibrous tissue, and proteoglycans are substances that help provide the cartilage\'s resilience.) Joints also have a lining (synovial tissue) that encloses them ',
