      title: 'Osteomyelitis - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 As the swollen tissue presses against the rigid',
      summary: 'As the swollen tissue presses against the rigid outer wall of the bone, the blood vessels in the bone marrow may become compressed, which reduces or cuts off the blood supply to th',
