      id: 'merck-home-topic-0087-chunk-0001',
      title: 'Tests for Musculoskeletal Disorders - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Tests for Musculoskeletal Disorders By Alexandra',
      summary: 'Tests for Musculoskeletal Disorders By Alexandra Villa-Forte , MD, MPH , Cleveland Clinic Reviewed/Revised Modified Feb 2024 v728699 Laboratory Tests | Imaging Tests | Other Diagno',
      steps: [
        'Laboratory tests , imaging tests , or other diagnostic procedures are sometimes necessary to help the doctor make or confirm a diagnosis.',
        'Laboratory Tests Lab Test Erythrocyte Sedimentation Rate (ESR) Laboratory tests are often helpful in making the diagnosis of a musculoskeletal disorder.',
        'For example, blood tests are done to measure the level of C-reactive protein (CRP) in the blood and the erythrocyte sedimentation rate (ESR), the rate at which red blood cells settle to the bottom of a test tube containing blood.',
        'The ESR and the CRP are usually increased when inflammation is present.',
      ],
