      title: 'Damage to Nerves in the Foot - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Damage to Nerves in the Foot (Interdigital Nerve',
      summary: 'Damage to Nerves in the Foot (Interdigital Nerve Pain; Interdigital Neuralgia; Morton Neuroma; Morton Neuralgia) By James C.',
      steps: [
        'Connors , DPM , Kent State University College of Podiatric Medicine Reviewed/Revised Modified Oct 2025 v26371036 Irritation of interdigital nerves (in the balls of the feet) may cause enlargement of those nerves, causing pain in the balls of the feet.',
        'Causes | Symptoms | Diagnosis | Treatment | Typical symptoms include a mild ache around the third or fourth toe that progresses to a burning or tingling sensation.',
        'The diagnosis is based on the person’s history and an examination of the foot.',
        'Modification of footwear, pads, and sometimes injection of a steroid (sometimes called a glucocorticoid or corticosteroid) can help relieve symptoms.',
