      title: 'Cubital Tunnel Syndrome - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 Because the ulnar nerve passes close to the surf',
      summary: 'Because the ulnar nerve passes close to the surface of the skin at the elbow (“funny bone”), it is easily damaged by repeatedly leaning on the elbow, by bending the elbow for prolo',
      steps: [
