      id: 'merck-home-topic-0113-chunk-0001',
      title: 'Dupuytren Contracture - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Dupuytren Contracture (Palmar Fibromatosis) By D',
      summary: 'Dupuytren Contracture (Palmar Fibromatosis) By David R.',
      steps: [
        'Steinberg , MD , Perelman School of Medicine at the University of Pennsylvania Reviewed/Revised Modified May 2024 v35322605 Dupuytren contracture is a progressive tightening of the bands of fibrous tissue (called fascia) inside the palms, causing a curling in of the fingers that eventually can result in a clawlike hand.',
        'Symptoms | Diagnosis | Treatment | Multimedia | Dupuytren contracture is one of the more common hand deformities, especially in men age 45 years or older.',
        'Typical symptoms include formation of a nodule in the palm and, eventually, curling in of the fingers.',
        'Doctors base the diagnosis on an examination of the hand.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
