  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0113-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Dupuytren Contracture - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 (See also Overview of Hand Disorders .) Dupuytre',
      summary: '(See also Overview of Hand Disorders .) Dupuytren contracture is one of the more common hand deformities and occurs more commonly in men, especially after age 45.',
      steps: [
        'Dupuytren contracture is more common among people with diabetes , alcohol use disorder , or epilepsy .',
        'The disorder is occasionally associated with other disorders, including thickening of fibrous tissue above the knuckles (Garrod pads), shrinking of fascia inside the penis that leads to deviated and painful erections (penile fibromatosis [ Peyronie disease ]), and, rarely, nodules on the soles of the feet (plantar fibromatosis).',
        'However, the specific factors that cause the fascia of the palm to thicken and curl in are unknown.',
        'Symptoms of Dupuytren Contracture Image The first symptom of Dupuytren contracture is usually a tender nodule in the palm (most often at the ring or small finger).',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
      escalation: '原始来源：MSD Manual / Dupuytren Contracture - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version',
