      title: 'Hand Abscess - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Hand Abscess By David R.',
      summary: 'Hand Abscess By David R.',
      steps: [
        'Steinberg , MD , Perelman School of Medicine at the University of Pennsylvania Reviewed/Revised Modified May 2024 v35322709 A hand abscess is an accumulation of pus affecting the hand, usually caused by a bacterial infection.',
        '(See also Overview of Hand Disorders .) Abscesses in the hands are fairly common and usually result from injury.',
        'A shallow (superficial) abscess may develop just under the skin anywhere in the hand and nearly always results from a minor injury, such as a splinter or needle prick.',
        'Severe pain, warmth, and redness develop over the abscess, often with swelling of lymph nodes in the armpit.',
      ],
