      steps: [
        'Steinberg , MD , Perelman School of Medicine at the University of Pennsylvania Reviewed/Revised Modified May 2024 v35322736 Diagnosis | Treatment | Multimedia | The most common human bite –related infection of the hand is injury to the knuckles of a person who punches another person in the mouth (called a clenched fist injury or fight bite).',
        'Animal bites are also common causes of hand infections.',
        'Wound contamination by a number of types of bacteria can result from human and animal bites.',
        'All bite injuries are potentially dangerous and can cause severe infections or serious complications (such as tendon infections or infectious arthritis ).',
