  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0120-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Kienböck Disease - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 Eventually, swelling occurs on top of the wrist,',
      summary: 'Eventually, swelling occurs on top of the wrist, which may become stiff.',
      steps: [
        'The disorder occurs in both hands in 10% of people.',
        'Diagnosis of Kienböck Disease Imaging tests Diagnosis of Kienböck disease is possible at an early stage by magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) or computed tomography (CT) and, if necessary, is later confirmed by x-rays .',
        'Treatment of Kienböck Disease Surgery Surgery is done to relieve pressure on the lunate bone, for example, by lengthening or shortening bones that connect to the lunate bone.',
        'Alternative surgical treatments are done in an attempt to reestablish the blood supply to the lunate bone (such as a bone graft or blood vessel graft).',
      ],
