      summary: 'Osteoarthritis of the Hand By David R.',
      steps: [
        'Steinberg , MD , Perelman School of Medicine at the University of Pennsylvania Reviewed/Revised Modified May 2024 v35322905 Osteoarthritis of the hand causes swelling, pain, and sometimes formation of cysts on the finger joints (particularly the outermost ones).',
        'Diagnosis | Treatment | Multimedia | Osteoarthritis of the hand causes bones over the outermost joints of the fingers (Heberden nodes) and the middle joints of the fingers (Bouchard nodes) to become larger.',
        'These joints and the base of the thumb become stiff and sometimes painful.',
        'The wrists and the joints between the fingers and hand are usually not affected.',
