      id: 'merck-home-topic-0123-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Radial Tunnel Syndrome - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 There is no numbness because the radial nerve ca',
      summary: 'There is no numbness because the radial nerve carries more fibers that control movement rather than sensation.',
      steps: [
        'In advanced cases, the muscles that straighten the thumb and fingers become weak.',
        'Doctors base the diagnosis of radial tunnel syndrome on an examination.',
        'Treatment of Radial Tunnel Syndrome A splint Sometimes surgery To reduce pressure on the nerve, the person should wear a splint on the wrist and/or the elbow and avoid rotating the wrist and bending the arm at the elbow.',
