  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0124-chunk-0001',
      title: 'Swan-Neck Deformity - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Swan-Neck Deformity By David R.',
      summary: 'Swan-Neck Deformity By David R.',
      steps: [
        'Steinberg , MD , Perelman School of Medicine at the University of Pennsylvania Reviewed/Revised Modified May 2024 v8984816 Swan-neck deformity is a bending in (flexion) of the base of the finger, a straightening out (extension) of the middle joint, and a bending in (flexion) of the outermost joint.',
        'Treatment | Multimedia | (See also Overview of Hand Disorders .) The most common cause of swan-neck deformity is rheumatoid arthritis .',
        'Other causes include untreated mallet finger , looseness (laxity) of the fibrous plate inside the hand at the base of the fingers or of the finger ligaments , chronic muscle spasm affecting the hands caused by nerve damage (called muscle spasticity), other types of arthritis, a ruptured finger tendon , and misalignment in the healing of a fracture of the middle bone of the finger.',
        'Normal bending of the finger may become impossible.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
