  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0126-chunk-0002',
      title: 'IgG4-Related Disease - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 Immunoglobulins are antibodies , which are prote',
      summary: 'Immunoglobulins are antibodies , which are proteins that are part of the body\'s immune system defenses.',
      steps: [
        'Immunoglobulins help protect against foreign or dangerous invaders, such as bacteria, viruses and cancer cells.',
        'The body produces thousands of different immunoglobulins, which are grouped into 5 classes (IgM, IgG, IgA, IgE, and IgD), some of which (eg, IgA and IgG) have subclasses.',
        'IgG4 is the least common of the 4 subclasses of IgG.',
        'It has various normal functions in the body, but in IgG4-related disease, immune cells that produce IgG4, along with other related cells, accumulate abnormally in certain organs and damage them.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
      escalation: '原始来源：MSD Manual / IgG4-Related Disease - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version',
