  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0128-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Neuropathic Arthropathy - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 The most commonly affected joints are The knee a',
      summary: 'The most commonly affected joints are The knee and ankle In people who have diabetes, the joints in the foot Often, only one area is affected, such as the foot and ankle, and usual',
      steps: [
        'Causes of Neuropathic Arthropathy When certain nerves are damaged, people may become unable to sense pain.',
        'A variety of disorders, such as diabetes mellitus, spinal cord disorders (such as injuries and fluid-filled cavities in the spinal cord [ syringomyelia ]), and syphilis , can damage these nerves.',
        'The most common causes are Diabetes Stroke People with nerve damage may injure a joint many times without noticing.',
        'Injuries may occur for years with accumulated joint damage before the joint malfunctions.',
      ],
