  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0130-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Overview of Spondyloarthritis - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 These disorders include Ankylosing spondylitis P',
      summary: 'These disorders include Ankylosing spondylitis Psoriatic arthritis Reactive arthritis Spondyloarthritis also can develop in association with inflammatory bowel disease (sometimes c',
      steps: [
        'Juvenile-onset spondyloarthritis affects the lower extremities, often affects joints on opposite sides of the body to different degrees, and begins most commonly in boys aged 7 to 16.',
        'Spondyloarthritis can also develop in people with no characteristics of other specific spondyloarthritis (undifferentiated spondyloarthritis).',
        'Treatment of undifferentiated spondyloarthritis is similar to treatment of reactive arthritis .',
        'The disease-modifying antirheumatic drugs (DMARDs) methotrexate and sulfasalazine may help relieve symptoms of spondyloarthritis but are often not as effective as methotrexate and sulfasalazine may help relieve symptoms of spondyloarthritis but are often not as effective as tumor necrosis factor inhibitors or other biologic agents .',
