  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0131-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Psoriatic Arthritis - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 Psoriatic arthritis occurs in about 20% of peopl',
      summary: 'Psoriatic arthritis occurs in about 20% of people with psoriasis (a skin condition causing flare-ups of red, scaly rashes and thickened, pitted nails).',
      steps: [
        'People with a certain gene ( HLA-B27 ) and those who have affected family members are at increased risk of psoriatic arthritis of the spine.',
        'The cause of psoriatic arthritis is unknown.',
        'Symptoms of Psoriatic Arthritis In psoriatic arthritis, inflammation often affects joints closest to the tips of the fingers and toes, although other joints, including the hips, knees, and spine, are often affected as well.',
        'Often, the joints of the upper extremities are affected more.',
      ],
