      id: 'merck-home-topic-0134-chunk-0001',
      title: 'Cervical Spinal Stenosis - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Cervical Spinal Stenosis By Peter J.',
      summary: 'Cervical Spinal Stenosis By Peter J.',
      steps: [
        'Moley , MD , Hospital for Special Surgery Reviewed/Revised Nov 2024 | Modified Jul 2025 v73501608 Cervical spinal stenosis is narrowing of the spinal canal in the neck.',
        'The narrowing squeezes (compresses) the nerves and sometimes the spinal cord causing neck pain and sometimes weakness and abnormal sensations in the arms or legs.',
        'Symptoms | Diagnosis | Treatment | Multimedia | Osteoarthritis , disc bulges and herniations, and spondylolisthesis can cause narrowing of the spinal canal.',
        'Symptoms, if present, can include neck pain ; tingling in the arm, hand, leg, or foot; and weakness and loss of balance.',
      ],
