  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0134-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Cervical Spinal Stenosis - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 The spinal nerves emerge from the sides through',
      summary: 'The spinal nerves emerge from the sides through spaces between the vertebrae to connect with nerves throughout the body.',
      steps: [
        'The part of the spinal nerve nearest the spinal cord is called the spinal nerve root.',
        'Because of their location, spinal nerve roots can be squeezed when the spinal canal is narrowed, resulting in pain.',
        'The most common causes of cervical spinal stenosis include osteoarthritis , disc degeneration, and spondylolisthesis .',
        'Other causes include ossification of the posterior longitudinal ligament, ankylosing spondylitis , and Paget disease of bone .',
      ],
