  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0135-chunk-0001',
      title: 'Herniated Disc - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Herniated Disc (Lumbar Disc Herniation; Herniate',
      summary: 'Herniated Disc (Lumbar Disc Herniation; Herniated, Ruptured, or Prolapsed Intervertebral Disc; Herniated Nucleus Pulposus) By Peter J.',
      steps: [
        'Moley , MD , Hospital for Special Surgery Reviewed/Revised Modified Nov 2024 v45388894 A herniated disc occurs when the tough covering of a disc in the spine tears or ruptures.',
        'The soft, jelly-like interior of the disc may then bulge out (herniate) through the covering.',
        'Symptoms | Diagnosis | Treatment | Prevention | Multimedia | Aging, injuries, and being overweight can cause a herniated disc.',
        'When herniated discs cause pain, it can be slight to debilitating.',
