      id: 'merck-home-topic-0140-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Spondylolisthesis - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 People who develop spondylolisthesis as adults a',
      summary: 'People who develop spondylolisthesis as adults are at risk of developing lumbar spinal stenosis .',
      steps: [
        'Symptoms of Spondylolisthesis Mild to moderate spondylolisthesis may cause little or no pain, particularly in young people.',
        'When pain occurs in adolescents, it is felt on only one side of the spine and may travel down a leg.',
        'The pain may accompany a fracture.',
        'When pain occurs in adults, it is felt over a specific part of the spine and travels down both legs.',
      ],
