      id: 'merck-home-topic-0143-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Fibromyalgia - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 Fibromyalgia and myofascial pain syndrome are no',
      summary: 'Fibromyalgia and myofascial pain syndrome are not strictly synonymous, but they are similar in that they both are central pain syndromes.',
      steps: [
        'But myofascial pain syndrome involves mostly muscle pain, and fibromyalgia causes more widespread body pain as well as other symptoms.',
        'Fibromyalgia is common.',
        'It is about 7 times more common among women.',
        'It usually occurs in young or middle-aged women but can also occur in men, children, and adolescents.',
      ],
