  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0146-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Osteonecrosis - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 The hip is most commonly affected, followed by t',
      summary: 'The hip is most commonly affected, followed by the knee and shoulder.',
      steps: [
        'The wrist and ankle are affected less often.',
        'Osteonecrosis does not usually affect the shoulder or other less commonly affected sites unless the hip is also affected.',
        'However, medication-related osteonecrosis of the jaw (MRONJ) is a disorder involving only the jaw bone.',
        'Causes of Osteonecrosis Osteonecrosis is not a specific disease but a condition in which death of the bone is confined to one or more specific (localized) areas.',
      ],
