  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0148-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Paget Disease of Bone - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 However, the overall prevalence of the disease s',
      summary: 'However, the overall prevalence of the disease seems to be decreasing.',
      steps: [
        'Men are more likely than women to develop Paget disease.',
        'The disease is most common in the United Kingdom and European countries including Spain, France, and Italy, as well as in countries settled by European immigrants (for example, Australia, New Zealand, the United States, and Canada).',
        'Paget disease is rare in Scandinavian countries and Asia.',
        'Causes of Paget Disease of Bone Normally, cells that break down old bone (osteoclasts) and cells that form new bone (osteoblasts) work in balance to maintain bone structure and integrity.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
