      title: 'Takayasu Arteritis - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Takayasu Arteritis (Pulseless Disease; Occlusive',
      summary: 'Takayasu Arteritis (Pulseless Disease; Occlusive Thromboaortopathy; Aortic Arch Syndrome; Takayasu\'s Arteritis) By Alexandra Villa-Forte , MD, MPH , Cleveland Clinic Reviewed/Revis',
      steps: [
        'Symptoms | Diagnosis | Treatment | Prognosis | More Information | The cause of Takayasu arteritis is unknown.',
        'People may have general symptoms, such as fever or muscle or joint aches, followed by specific symptoms depending on which organs are affected.',
        'An imaging test of the aorta is done to confirm the diagnosis.',
        'A corticosteroid and sometimes another medication that suppresses the immune system can usually control the inflammation.',
