      id: 'merck-home-topic-0173-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Takayasu Arteritis - Bone, Joint, and Muscle Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 The aorta and its branches, including arteries t',
      summary: 'The aorta and its branches, including arteries that take blood to the head and the kidneys, become inflamed.',
      steps: [
        'In about half of people, the pulmonary arteries (that carry blood from the heart to the lungs) are also affected.',
        'Inflammation may cause sections of these arteries to become narrow or blocked.',
        'The walls of the aorta or its branches may thicken, resulting in a bulge (aneurysm).',
        'The affected arteries cannot provide enough blood to the tissues they supply.',
      ],
