      id: 'merck-home-topic-0174-chunk-0001',
      title: 'Autonomic Neuropathies - Brain, Spinal Cord, and Nerve Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Autonomic Neuropathies By Elizabeth Coon , MD ,',
      summary: 'Autonomic Neuropathies By Elizabeth Coon , MD , Mayo Clinic Reviewed/Revised May 2025 | Modified Jul 2025 v746474 Autonomic neuropathies are disorders affecting the peripheral nerv',
      steps: [
        'Causes | Symptoms | Diagnosis | Treatment | Causes include diabetes, amyloidosis, autoimmune disorders, cancer, excessive alcohol consumption, and certain medications.',
        'People may feel light-headed when they stand and have urination problems, constipation, and vomiting, and men may have erectile dysfunction.',
        'Doctors do a physical examination and various tests to check for autonomic malfunction and possible causes.',
        'The cause is corrected or treated if possible.',
