  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0176-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Multiple System Atrophy (MSA) - Brain, Spinal Cord, and Nerve Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 Simple measures and medications can help lessen',
      summary: 'Simple measures and medications can help lessen symptoms, but the disorder is progressive and ultimately fatal.',
      steps: [
        '(See also Overview of the Autonomic Nervous System .) Multiple system atrophy usually begins when people are in their 50s.',
        'It affects men and women equally.',
        'There are 2 types of multiple system atrophy (MSA), based on which symptoms occur first: MSA-C is characterized by loss of coordination and difficulty maintaining balance, which indicates cerebellar dysfunction (indicated by the C).',
        'MSA-P is very similar to Parkinson disease (indicated by the P) except that the usual tremor often does not develop and levodopa often does not relieve symptoms.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
