  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0177-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Overview of the Autonomic Nervous System - Brain, Spinal Cord, and Nerve Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 The autonomic nervous system has two main divisi',
      summary: 'The autonomic nervous system has two main divisions: Sympathetic Parasympathetic The autonomic nervous system receives information about the body and external environment and respo',
      steps: [
        'An autonomic nerve pathway involves 2 nerve cells.',
        'One cell is located in the brain stem or spinal cord.',
        'It is connected by nerve fibers to the other cell located in a cluster of nerve cells (called an autonomic ganglion).',
        'Nerve fibers from these ganglia connect with internal organs.',
      ],
