      summary: 'Pure Autonomic Failure By Elizabeth Coon , MD , Mayo Clinic Reviewed/Revised May 2025 | Modified Jul 2025 v746539 Pure autonomic failure is dysfunction of many of the processes con',
      steps: [
        'Symptoms | Diagnosis | Treatment | Pure autonomic failure is caused by abnormal accumulation of alpha-synuclein (a protein that helps brain cells communicate) in the brain.',
