  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0183-chunk-0001',
      title: 'Spinal Cord - Brain, Spinal Cord, and Nerve Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Spinal Cord By Mark Freedman , MD, MSc , Univers',
      summary: 'Spinal Cord By Mark Freedman , MD, MSc , University of Ottawa Reviewed/Revised Modified Apr 2025 v733480 Multimedia | The spinal cord is a long, fragile tubelike structure that beg',
      steps: [
        'The spinal cord consists of bundles of nerve axons forming pathways that carry incoming and outgoing messages between the brain and the rest of the body.',
        'The spinal cord contains nerve cell circuits that control coordinated movements such as walking and swimming, as well as urinating.',
        'It is also the center for reflexes, such as the knee jerk reflex (see figure Reflex Arc: A No-Brainer ).',
        'Like the brain, the spinal cord is covered by 3 layers of tissue ( meninges ).',
      ],
