      id: 'merck-home-topic-0185-chunk-0001',
      title: 'Amnesia - Brain, Spinal Cord, and Nerve Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Amnesia By Juebin Huang , MD, PhD , Department o',
      summary: 'Amnesia By Juebin Huang , MD, PhD , Department of Neurology, University of Mississippi Medical Center Reviewed/Revised Sept 2025 | Modified Feb 2026 v9051969 Amnesia is total or pa',
      steps: [
        'Causes | Symptoms | Diagnosis | Treatment | Multimedia | Because many areas of the brain are involved in memory, damage almost anywhere in the brain can cause amnesia.',
        'How amnesia is caused is only partly understood.',
        'How long memory loss lasts depends on the severity of the damage that caused it.',
        'Doctors evaluate memory loss by asking simple questions and doing formal tests of memory.',
      ],
