      title: 'Apraxia - Brain, Spinal Cord, and Nerve Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Apraxia By Juebin Huang , MD, PhD , Department o',
      summary: 'Apraxia By Juebin Huang , MD, PhD , Department of Neurology, University of Mississippi Medical Center Reviewed/Revised Modified Sept 2025 v26414464 Apraxia is loss of the ability t',
      steps: [
        'Causes | Symptoms | Diagnosis | Treatment | Prognosis | People with apraxia cannot carry out the sequence of movements needed to complete simple skilled or complex tasks, even though they are physically able to do the tasks.',
        'Doctors ask the person to do or imitate common learned tasks.',
        'Tests of brain function and imaging tests may be done.',
        'Physical and occupational therapists can help by making the environment safer and by providing devices to enable people with apraxia function better.',
