  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0188-chunk-0001',
      title: 'Brain Dysfunction by Location - Brain, Spinal Cord, and Nerve Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Brain Dysfunction by Location By Juebin Huang ,',
      summary: 'Brain Dysfunction by Location By Juebin Huang , MD, PhD , Department of Neurology, University of Mississippi Medical Center Reviewed/Revised Modified Sept 2025 v736680 Frontal Lobe',
      steps: [
        'Parts of the Brain Which side of the brain is affected is also important because the functions of the 2 halves of the cerebrum (cerebral hemispheres) are not identical.',
        'Some functions of the brain are performed exclusively by 1 hemisphere.',
        'For example, movement and sensation on 1 side of the body are controlled by the hemisphere on the opposite side.',
        'Other functions are performed mainly by 1 hemisphere, which is said to be dominant for that function, and the other hemisphere is said to be nondominant.',
      ],
