  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0189-chunk-0001',
      title: 'Brain Dysfunction Related to COVID-19 - Brain, Spinal Cord, and Nerve Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #1 Brain Dysfunction Related to COVID-19 By Juebin',
      summary: 'Brain Dysfunction Related to COVID-19 By Juebin Huang , MD, PhD , Department of Neurology, University of Mississippi Medical Center Reviewed/Revised Modified Sept 2025 v60529901 Sy',
      steps: [
        'However, COVID-19 sometimes affects many parts of the body and can cause many other symptoms.',
        'It can affect the brain and nerves, causing neurologic symptoms , such as confusion.',
        'COVID-19 can also cause disturbances in thinking, emotion, mood, and/or behavior, causing mental health (psychological) symptoms.',
        'Neurologic and psychological symptoms may occur when people are first infected with COVID-19, while people are recovering, and/or after people have recovered from the initial infection.',
      ],
      contraindications: const <String>[],
      escalation: '原始来源：MSD Manual / Brain Dysfunction Related to COVID-19 - Brain, Spinal Cord, and Nerve Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version',
