  KnowledgeEntry(
      id: 'merck-home-topic-0189-chunk-0002',
      title: 'Brain Dysfunction Related to COVID-19 - Brain, Spinal Cord, and Nerve Disorders - MSD Manual Consumer Version #2 After recovering from the initial infection with',
      summary: 'After recovering from the initial infection with COVID-19, people may have persistent symptoms, such as fatigue, impaired memory and cognition, headache, numbness and tingling, and',
      steps: [
        'Doctors may do magnetic resonance imaging to check for changes in the brain and do blood and urine tests to rule out other disorders that can cause similar symptoms.',
        'The main treatment for neurologic and psychological symptoms is supportive care, but for people with depression, antidepressants may be useful.',
        'Neurologic and psychological symptoms may last a long time—for many weeks to months.',
        'Symptoms that occur during the first 4 weeks after the initial infection are called acute COVID-19.',
      ],
